package com.redhat.coolstore.persistence;

import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;
import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Named;
import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;
import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;

@Dependent
public class Resources {

    @PersistenceContext
    private EntityManager em;

    @Named
    public EntityManager getEntityManager() {
        return em;
    }
}
```

## Additional Information (optional)
Note that in Quarkus, it's recommended to use CDI (Context and Dependency Injection) annotations instead of JPA (Java Persistence API) annotations. However, in this case, we are only addressing the specific issue mentioned, and the `@PersistenceContext` annotation is still valid. If you plan to migrate the entire application to Quarkus, you may need to consider replacing JPA annotations with CDI annotations in the future.
